													</UML:ModelElement.stereotype>
													<UML:ModelElement.taggedValue>
														<UML:TaggedValue tag="documentation" value="&lt;font color=&quot;#4f81bd&quot;&gt;PhysicalDescription&lt;/font&gt; is a class that describes the numeric physical properties of a geologic unit (&lt;font color=&quot;#4f81bd&quot;&gt;GeologicUnit&lt;/font&gt;) earth material (&lt;font color=&quot;#4f81bd&quot;&gt;EarthMaterial&lt;/font&gt; ), or geologic structure (&lt;font color=&quot;#4f81bd&quot;&gt;GeologicStructure&lt;/font&gt;) (e.g., density, porosity, magnetic susceptibility, remanent magnetism).  These properties are modelled here as scalar numeric values (&lt;font color=&quot;#4f81bd&quot;&gt;SWE::Quantity&lt;/font&gt;).&#xA;"/>
														<UML:TaggedValue tag="isSpecification" value="false"/>
