															<UML:ModelElement.taggedValue>
																<UML:TaggedValue tag="description" value="The &lt;font color=&quot;#4f81bd&quot;&gt;unitComposition&lt;/font&gt; property (&lt;font color=&quot;#4f81bd&quot;&gt;SWE::Category&lt;/font&gt;) provides a term from a composition-based classification that requires summarising the overall character of the unit.  It is not applicable at the rock material or specimen level. Examples are: alkalic, subaluminous, peraluminous, I-Type, carbonate, phosphate.&#xA;"/>
